The allowlist pattern for `role` (`VALID_ROLES.has(role)`) is strictly safer than a blocklist (trying to reject bad characters). Allowlists reject everything unknown by default; blocklists fail open when an attacker finds a bypass. This applies to file extensions, HTTP methods, content types -- anywhere you're validating categorical input.
